WEBVTT

00:02.580 --> 00:04.620
Dre: People always say
 they hate being labeled.

00:04.620 --> 00:07.380
They don't want to be seen
 as just one thing.

00:07.380 --> 00:09.670
But let's be honest --
 we need labels.

00:09.670 --> 00:12.040
When things
 aren't clearly labeled,

00:12.040 --> 00:13.290
it can cause problems.

00:13.290 --> 00:15.000
Come on!

00:15.000 --> 00:17.920
Who put the mom jeans
in the men's section?!

00:17.920 --> 00:19.250
And even in families,

00:19.250 --> 00:21.330
labels can be
 a pretty useful shorthand.

00:31.290 --> 00:33.790
But sometimes people --
 just like pants --

00:33.790 --> 00:35.920
have the wrong label...

00:35.920 --> 00:38.420
while others act in ways
 that surprise you.

00:38.420 --> 00:40.250
[ Siren wails ]
 [ Screams ]

00:40.250 --> 00:42.620
And that's when things
 get confusing.

00:42.620 --> 00:43.830
[ Screams ]

00:48.540 --> 00:50.830
♪♪

00:50.830 --> 00:52.120
Oh. Mom.
 Yes.

00:52.120 --> 00:53.620
Uh, which one
for Laura's party --

00:53.620 --> 00:54.710
this one or this one?

00:54.710 --> 00:56.670
I like that one!
 Okay, great.

00:56.670 --> 00:58.170
[ Chuckles ]

00:58.170 --> 01:00.170
What? Wait, what are you do--
That's my shirt!

01:00.170 --> 01:02.000
Ugh!

01:02.000 --> 01:03.580
She's doing you a favor,
baby.

01:03.580 --> 01:04.330
Up top.

01:04.330 --> 01:05.459
Okay.
 Mm!

01:05.459 --> 01:07.040
What kind of party
is this gonna be?

01:07.040 --> 01:08.000
Who's gonna be there?

01:08.000 --> 01:09.580
What time
are you coming home?

01:09.580 --> 01:11.080
Dad,
can you check her?

01:11.080 --> 01:13.620
Bow, the girl is about to go
to college, okay?
 Mm-hmm.

01:13.620 --> 01:16.460
It's basically a courtesy
that she's even asking us.

01:16.460 --> 01:18.170
She could've lied
and said she's gonna study.

01:18.170 --> 01:19.790
Could've. Didn't.

01:19.790 --> 01:20.960
You're welcome.

01:20.960 --> 01:23.040
Up top again.
 So annoying.

01:23.040 --> 01:25.500
Hey! Junior.
Come over here.

01:25.500 --> 01:26.880
Why?
 You want to go out
tonight?

01:26.880 --> 01:28.920
Sure. What are you
in the mood for?

01:28.920 --> 01:30.750
Dinner, a show?

01:30.750 --> 01:33.170
It's been forever
since we went dancing.

01:33.170 --> 01:35.040
[ Laughs ]
That was so much fun!

01:35.040 --> 01:36.250
No, I meant
with your sister.

01:36.250 --> 01:37.710
You want to go
to a party?

01:37.710 --> 01:39.120
Ooh!
 What?! Why?!

01:39.120 --> 01:40.710
Is this
because of the shirt?

01:40.710 --> 01:42.460
It's not not
 because of the shirt.

01:42.460 --> 01:44.460
You guys are gonna have
so much fun. Huh?

01:44.460 --> 01:45.380
Trust me.

01:45.380 --> 01:46.960
I'm in,
so long as you and I

01:46.960 --> 01:49.420
are still on for tomorrow
at the farmers market.

01:49.420 --> 01:50.500
[ Chuckles ]

01:50.500 --> 01:52.250
I've got my eye
on some local honey

01:52.250 --> 01:54.170
that will help
with my allergies.

01:54.170 --> 01:56.000
I'm gonna go get changed.
 Mm-hmm.

01:56.000 --> 01:58.040
This is so unfair.
 Really?

01:58.040 --> 01:59.040
It is.

01:59.040 --> 02:01.500
He's a lame.
 Exactly.

02:01.500 --> 02:05.460
And I want him
to keep an eye on her.

02:05.460 --> 02:06.540
Bow.
 Ha.

02:06.540 --> 02:07.750
She's got a good head
on her shoulders.

02:07.750 --> 02:09.169
We can trust her.

02:09.169 --> 02:11.790
Look, Dre, it is
the end of senior year.

02:11.790 --> 02:14.540
Mm-hmm.
 This is when
all these kids slip up.

02:14.540 --> 02:17.790
They think they're grown,
but they're still dumb kids.

02:17.790 --> 02:19.540
She's 17 years old, Dre.
 Yes.

02:19.540 --> 02:22.290
[ Scoffs ] I remember
where I was at 17.

02:22.290 --> 02:24.250
The library.
 Yes!

02:24.250 --> 02:26.960
Why would you
s-say it like that?

02:26.960 --> 02:28.710
He's gonna
embarrass her, Bow.

02:28.710 --> 02:30.170
He's not gonna
embarrass her.
 What?

02:30.170 --> 02:33.250
Okay. Party cloak
or formal cloak?

02:33.250 --> 02:35.420
I don't want to look like
I'm trying too hard.

02:35.420 --> 02:39.040
♪♪

02:39.040 --> 02:39.960
[ Hushed ] Lame.

02:41.580 --> 02:42.960
Was that an "L"?

02:42.960 --> 02:44.670
Yeah,
for "I love you, Junior."

02:44.670 --> 02:46.290
[ Chuckles ]
He loves you so much.

02:46.290 --> 02:47.380
Party cloak, sweetie.

02:47.380 --> 02:49.000
The purple --
it'll bring out your eyes.

02:51.290 --> 02:52.670
♪ Tell me when to go ♪

02:52.670 --> 02:53.830
♪ Tell me when to go ♪

02:53.830 --> 02:54.790
♪ Tell me when to go ♪

02:54.790 --> 02:56.170
♪ Tell me when to go ♪

02:56.170 --> 03:00.380
♪ Go dumb, dumb,
dumb, dumb, dumb ♪

03:00.380 --> 03:01.830
Yeah?
 Hey, Pops.

03:01.830 --> 03:02.830
What the hell's
going on over here, man?

03:02.830 --> 03:03.960
Nothing.

03:03.960 --> 03:05.460
♪ Tell me when to go ♪

03:05.460 --> 03:07.170
Are you playing E-40?

03:07.170 --> 03:09.380
No!
 I didn't know
you liked E-40.

03:09.380 --> 03:11.330
Pops, I like E-40.
 No, you don't.

03:11.330 --> 03:13.380
Yes, I --
 We'll keep the music down.

03:13.380 --> 03:14.920
"We"?
 [ Sighs ]

03:14.920 --> 03:16.250
You got somebody over here?
 No.

03:16.250 --> 03:18.170
Oh, hey.

03:18.170 --> 03:19.920
Rhonda? I didn't even know
you were in town.

03:19.920 --> 03:21.540
What the hell
you doing here?

03:21.540 --> 03:24.540
Dad and I are on the mission to
find the best sandwich in L.A.

03:24.540 --> 03:26.250
I like sandwiches.
 You don't like sandwiches.

03:26.250 --> 03:27.380
Yes, I do.
 No, you don't.

03:29.080 --> 03:31.290
Okay.
I see how it is.

03:31.290 --> 03:33.290
Always the two of you.

03:33.290 --> 03:35.420
All right, well, look,
could you keep the music down?

03:35.420 --> 03:37.500
This is
a civilized community.

03:37.500 --> 03:38.750
Sure thing, boss.

03:40.290 --> 03:41.790
♪ Tell me when to go ♪

03:41.790 --> 03:43.330
♪ Tell me when to go ♪

03:43.330 --> 03:45.040
♪ Tell me when to go ♪
 I love that song.

03:45.040 --> 03:46.920
♪ Go dumb, dumb,
dumb, dumb, dumb ♪

03:50.710 --> 03:52.210
You found me!
 Oh, my God!

03:52.210 --> 03:54.120
I've been hiding
for two hours.

03:54.120 --> 03:55.540
Ohh!
 Two!

03:55.540 --> 03:58.000
Did you find Jack yet?
 Uh, I'm still
looking for him.

03:58.000 --> 03:59.290
[ Laughs ]

03:59.290 --> 04:00.670
You weren't looking,
were you?

04:00.670 --> 04:03.250
Mm?
 You forgot.

04:03.250 --> 04:06.210
Okay, yes, I did.
I forgot.

04:06.210 --> 04:09.210
I have a growing parasite
inside my belly

04:09.210 --> 04:11.670
that is sucking
all the power from my brain.

04:11.670 --> 04:14.380
[ Voice breaking ]
So you just need to lower
your expectations, okay?

04:14.380 --> 04:16.920
Mommy's doing her best.

04:16.920 --> 04:19.329
Why do they tell women
they can have it all?

04:19.329 --> 04:20.579
Did I win?

04:20.579 --> 04:23.830
I've been hiding in the dryer
for 2 1/2 hours.

04:23.830 --> 04:25.750
Mom stopped looking
for us.

04:25.750 --> 04:26.920
We're forgotten children.

04:28.960 --> 04:31.580
Which means
no one will know

04:31.580 --> 04:33.170
if we do the things

04:33.170 --> 04:35.290
that they always tell us
  not to do.

04:35.290 --> 04:37.790
You mean like
join the white man's army?

04:37.790 --> 04:40.080
You've been hanging out
with Pops too much.

04:40.080 --> 04:44.170
So, what should
we do first?

04:44.170 --> 04:46.620
Mom said never to lay a finger
on that vase!

04:46.620 --> 04:48.330
But we're
motherless children.

04:48.330 --> 04:49.830
Catch!

04:51.210 --> 04:52.670
[ Grunting ]

04:52.670 --> 04:54.420
♪ Hey, hey, hey ♪

04:54.420 --> 04:55.540
♪ Bounce with me ♪

04:55.540 --> 04:56.960
♪ Hey ♪

04:56.960 --> 04:58.580
♪ I'm goin' postal, global ♪

04:58.580 --> 04:59.710
♪ Coast to coast like... ♪

04:59.710 --> 05:02.670
[ Indistinct conversations ]

05:02.670 --> 05:04.380
Wow!
This is festive!

05:04.380 --> 05:07.670
I'd like to find Laura's parents
and thank them.

05:07.670 --> 05:09.750
Do you think
they're upstairs or downstairs?

05:09.750 --> 05:11.210
Or in St. Lucia.

05:11.210 --> 05:12.170
Hey!
 Young woman: Hi, Zoey!

05:12.170 --> 05:15.000
There are
no parents here?

05:15.000 --> 05:17.420
But there are
 some adults present,

05:17.420 --> 05:19.880
like an aunt
or a trusted nanny...?

05:19.880 --> 05:21.420
Nope -- just that guy

05:21.420 --> 05:23.500
who graduated from our school
two years ago.

05:26.380 --> 05:28.620
Okay.
Dude, I'm begging you.

05:28.620 --> 05:30.750
Please try
and be cool.

05:30.750 --> 05:32.210
Not a problem.

05:32.210 --> 05:33.500
I am cool!

05:33.500 --> 05:35.500
[ Laughs ]

05:35.500 --> 05:37.790
Yes! Fruit punch!
Yeah!

05:39.120 --> 05:40.170
[ Chuckles nervously ]
I'm not with him.

05:40.170 --> 05:40.960
Zoey!

05:43.920 --> 05:45.290
Zoey?

05:45.290 --> 05:48.330
I hate to be the bearer
of bad news, but...

05:48.330 --> 05:50.540
this punch
smells like Pops' room.

05:50.540 --> 05:52.000
I think
there's alcohol in it.

05:52.000 --> 05:54.380
Okay, dude, this is
a high-school party,

05:54.380 --> 05:55.920
so chill out.

05:55.920 --> 05:58.290
You don't
have to drink it.

05:58.290 --> 05:59.330
All right.

05:59.330 --> 06:00.960
I read about this.

06:00.960 --> 06:03.120
It was bound to happen
sometime.

06:03.120 --> 06:04.880
Keep a cool head.

06:04.880 --> 06:06.330
I'm at a rager.

06:06.330 --> 06:08.250
Oh, my God.
 [ Exhales ]

06:08.250 --> 06:10.790
You're the reason
they should bring bullying back.

06:12.960 --> 06:14.540
Joke's on you.

06:14.540 --> 06:15.880
Never went away.

06:15.880 --> 06:18.120
Ha ha!

06:18.120 --> 06:20.080
[ Laughs ]
 I ain't believe that.

06:20.080 --> 06:21.750
Dre. Me and Rhonda are
going down to the track.

06:21.750 --> 06:23.080
You got some extra cash?

06:23.080 --> 06:25.670
Grown-ass man
asking his son for money.

06:25.670 --> 06:27.290
Get a job, Earl!

06:27.290 --> 06:29.540
Hey, Mama, don't talk to him
like that.
 What?

06:29.540 --> 06:31.170
This man put food
on our table.

06:31.170 --> 06:33.880
He worked his ass off
for this family

06:33.880 --> 06:36.120
until he sued
that mattress company
for reparations.

06:36.120 --> 06:37.790
That's right.
Thank you, Rhonda.
 Uh-huh.

06:37.790 --> 06:41.120
Yeah, I was a breadwinner
  and a civil-rights pioneer.

06:41.120 --> 06:43.960
And now that I'm retired,
I've taken up mentoring

06:43.960 --> 06:46.620
several inexperienced gamblers
down at Hollywood Park.

06:46.620 --> 06:48.120
That's my daddy --
philanthropic.

06:48.120 --> 06:49.250
Still giving back.

06:49.250 --> 06:51.790
Whatever. Pops,
I ain't got nothin' on me.

06:51.790 --> 06:53.460
That's okay --
I know where you keep the money

06:53.460 --> 06:54.500
hidden in your drawer
upstairs.

06:54.500 --> 06:55.920
Unh-unh, Earl!

06:55.920 --> 06:58.290
Dre's cupcake money
is my petty cash!

06:58.290 --> 07:00.330
Earl!

07:00.330 --> 07:01.790
Oh, Earl!

07:03.710 --> 07:05.580
Why do you always
defend him?

07:05.580 --> 07:07.210
Come on, Dre. We both have
our favorite parent.

07:07.210 --> 07:08.290
You chose Mom.

07:08.290 --> 07:10.120
That wasn't even
a choice.

07:10.120 --> 07:11.500
She's the good one.

07:11.500 --> 07:16.580
Dad cheats on everything --
his taxes, his wife, Monopoly.

07:16.580 --> 07:18.920
The man keeps a Park Place card
in his pocket.

07:18.920 --> 07:20.500
Dude,
Mom's hardly a saint.

07:20.500 --> 07:22.170
What has she ever done?!

07:22.170 --> 07:24.880
Okay, well, I don't know --
she blew up Dad's boat.

07:24.880 --> 07:26.120
Mm-hmm.
 Shot him.

07:26.120 --> 07:27.920
Mm-hmm.
 Blew up his other boat.

07:27.920 --> 07:29.290
Mm-hmm.
 Shot him again.

07:30.290 --> 07:31.580
You reachin'.

07:33.080 --> 07:35.210
She had an affair
with Mr. Caldwell.

07:35.210 --> 07:36.830
[ Laughs ]

07:36.830 --> 07:38.170
My gym teacher?

07:38.170 --> 07:41.460
[ Laughs ]
No. No. No way. No way.

07:41.460 --> 07:43.790
Now, how you think
you got an "A" in gym?

07:43.790 --> 07:44.790
I --

07:44.790 --> 07:47.120
[ Grunting ]

07:47.120 --> 07:49.750
Attaboy, Dre.
You got it.

07:49.750 --> 07:50.830
Thanks, Coach Dad.

07:54.380 --> 07:56.250
No wonder
he had Thanksgiving with us.

07:56.250 --> 07:58.500
♪♪

08:00.330 --> 08:01.790
[ Voice breaking ]
Mama, can I ask you something?

08:06.380 --> 08:07.620
This is totally normal.

08:07.620 --> 08:08.920
Not a big deal.

08:08.920 --> 08:11.080
[ Chuckles ]
Just a few bad apples.

08:12.790 --> 08:15.290
Oh, my God.
My student body cabinet?!

08:15.290 --> 08:17.210
Drew,
you're the treasurer!

08:17.210 --> 08:19.920
Have you been
treasuring drunk?

08:19.920 --> 08:22.460
Emily! You're
the designated survivor!

08:22.460 --> 08:24.330
We can't both be here!

08:24.330 --> 08:26.960
Relax, dude.
Have a beer.

08:26.960 --> 08:29.210
I don't need to be drunk
to be cool.

08:29.210 --> 08:31.380
The new drunk
is not being drunk.

08:31.380 --> 08:32.669
Okay?

08:32.669 --> 08:34.919
[ Scoffs ] Beer.

08:34.919 --> 08:36.330
You know that those are
covered in weed?

08:36.330 --> 08:38.620
[ Scoffs ] Okay.

08:38.620 --> 08:39.750
No, dude,
you're gonna die.

08:42.789 --> 08:45.080
Oh, my God. How many
am I supposed to have?

08:45.080 --> 08:46.460
I don't know,

08:46.460 --> 08:49.000
but that kid over there
only had one.

08:49.000 --> 08:51.750
Aaaaah!

08:51.750 --> 08:53.420
Aaaaah!

08:53.420 --> 08:55.500
Oh, no. Oh, no!

08:55.500 --> 08:57.290
My brain hasn't
finished forming yet.

08:57.290 --> 08:58.540
I got to throw these up.

08:58.540 --> 09:01.620
[ Retching ]

09:01.620 --> 09:03.420
Why can't I
throw these up?!

09:03.420 --> 09:06.040
Does anyone here
have a tongue depressor?

09:06.040 --> 09:08.670
[ Laughter ]
 Why are you all just laughing?!

09:11.210 --> 09:12.710
Mama.
 Mm?

09:12.710 --> 09:14.670
You wouldn't believe
what Rhonda just said about you.

09:14.670 --> 09:18.000
She said you ran around on Pops
with my teacher.

09:18.000 --> 09:19.830
What?!
Oh, honey, you --

09:19.830 --> 09:22.380
[ Scoffs ]
You know that's not true.

09:22.380 --> 09:23.750
Okay, well,
why would she lie?

09:23.750 --> 09:25.330
Everybody lies.

09:25.330 --> 09:27.960
Bill Clinton, Zac Efron.

09:27.960 --> 09:30.080
And don't get me started
on Oprah.

09:30.080 --> 09:32.460
"Lose weight eating bread,"
my ass!

09:32.460 --> 09:35.000
Even Archbishop Desmond Tutu
lies.

09:35.000 --> 09:37.040
I was sitting on an airplane
with him one time.

09:37.040 --> 09:40.210
Went to the bathroom,
came back, my peanuts were gone.

09:40.210 --> 09:41.540
And I said to him...

09:41.540 --> 09:45.290
Desmond Tutu,
did you steal my peanuts?!

09:45.290 --> 09:48.080
Ma'am,
my is Ahmad Rashad,

09:48.080 --> 09:49.790
and your hand
is on my penis.

09:49.790 --> 09:51.670
[ Gasps ] Oh.

09:51.670 --> 09:53.580
Well...

09:53.580 --> 09:55.960
Mama, what are you
talking about?

09:55.960 --> 09:57.540
I'm talking about lies!

09:57.540 --> 10:00.790
Like the one your sister told
about me and your gym teacher!

10:00.790 --> 10:01.880
Hold on.

10:01.880 --> 10:03.080
What?

10:03.080 --> 10:06.120
I never said
  "gym teacher."

10:07.750 --> 10:11.420
Mama, you were running around
on Pops with Coach Dad?

10:11.420 --> 10:15.000
Now I realize I was the only one
calling him Coach Dad!

10:15.000 --> 10:17.210
Mama, how could you?!
 Oh, boy,
don't make such a fuss.

10:17.210 --> 10:19.710
It was a hundred years ago,
and it was just one time.

10:19.710 --> 10:21.920
One time?
 And then on and off
for about two years.

10:21.920 --> 10:23.500
What?!
 Oh, come on, boy.

10:23.500 --> 10:25.460
How do you think
you passed gym class?

10:28.420 --> 10:31.540
Because I ran the mile
in under 22 minutes.

10:31.540 --> 10:33.500
♪♪

10:33.500 --> 10:35.380
It's fun when no one
cares about you.

10:35.380 --> 10:36.920
Mm-hmm.
 What's next?

10:36.920 --> 10:41.710
Well, we've taken Mom's youth,
her joy, and her beauty.

10:41.710 --> 10:44.120
And now it's time
to take her Enclave.

10:44.120 --> 10:45.750
♪ Hit it ♪

10:45.750 --> 10:48.500
[ Rob Base and DJ E-Z Rock's
"It Takes Two" plays ]

10:51.330 --> 10:52.330
♪ It takes two... ♪

10:52.330 --> 10:53.670
Let's kick it up
a notch.

10:55.710 --> 10:57.420
♪ It takes two
to make it outta sight ♪

10:59.540 --> 11:00.420
[ Both laugh ]

11:02.250 --> 11:04.250
Whoo! Come on!
Faster! Faster!

11:04.250 --> 11:06.880
♪ One, two, three,
get loose now ♪

11:06.880 --> 11:08.920
One...

11:08.920 --> 11:09.790
two...

11:09.790 --> 11:11.170
and three!

11:11.170 --> 11:12.880
Whoo!

11:12.880 --> 11:14.830
Oh!

11:14.830 --> 11:16.830
Yeah!

11:16.830 --> 11:19.000
♪ It takes two
to make a thing ♪

11:19.000 --> 11:19.790
Again!

11:21.620 --> 11:24.500
Junior, stop being
so self-conscious.

11:24.500 --> 11:26.290
No one is looking
at you.

11:26.290 --> 11:27.460
Are you sure?

11:27.460 --> 11:28.880
Positive.

11:28.880 --> 11:30.580
Just have fun,
 sweetheart.

11:30.580 --> 11:33.080
And call me if your sister does
anything stupid.

11:33.080 --> 11:34.710
Mm-hmm.

11:34.710 --> 11:37.460
Oh, my God.
Junior! Are you high?

11:37.460 --> 11:38.920
Yes.

11:38.920 --> 11:41.880
Did you know these chips are
laced with cannabinoids?

11:41.880 --> 11:43.580
[ Laughs ]
 Uh, yeah.

11:43.580 --> 11:46.880
Rastaman's Pot-a-to Chips
have weed in them.

11:46.880 --> 11:47.790
Ohhhh!

11:47.790 --> 11:49.580
How many of these
did you have?

11:49.580 --> 11:51.960
[ Chuckles ]
You talk white.

11:51.960 --> 11:53.080
[ Chuckles ]

11:53.080 --> 11:54.620
And Mom thinks
  I'm the problem.

11:54.620 --> 11:56.210
[ Chuckling ]
Hey, Mr. President.

11:56.210 --> 11:58.540
Can I get one for the 'Gram?
Shirt off.

11:58.540 --> 12:00.170
Okay.
 [ Laughs ]

12:00.170 --> 12:01.920
Riley! Knock it off.

12:01.920 --> 12:04.210
That's my brother,
and I will ruin you.

12:04.210 --> 12:05.880
Junior,
put your clothes on.

12:05.880 --> 12:08.040
Let me give the people
what they want!

12:08.040 --> 12:09.040
You're a mess.

12:09.040 --> 12:10.540
Um...here.

12:10.540 --> 12:11.960
Drink all of this.

12:11.960 --> 12:13.120
Cops!

12:13.120 --> 12:15.170
Oh, God!
Come on! We have to go!

12:15.170 --> 12:16.460
Wait.
Where are your shoes?

12:16.460 --> 12:18.040
Where are
  anybody's shoes?

12:18.040 --> 12:20.580
Okay. I'll find them.

12:20.580 --> 12:22.250
I don't need shoes.

12:22.250 --> 12:24.750
I have no feet!

12:24.750 --> 12:26.620
Oh! Found them!

12:26.620 --> 12:28.170
We've got to g--

12:28.170 --> 12:29.210
Junior?!

12:29.210 --> 12:30.960
[ Police radio chatter ]

12:33.750 --> 12:36.380
Hello, officers.
I am so glad you're here.

12:36.380 --> 12:37.960
I heard there's alcohol
at this party.

12:37.960 --> 12:39.170
♪♪

12:43.080 --> 12:45.040
I'd been thinking.

12:45.040 --> 12:47.000
After all my mom went through
 with Pops, who was I to judge?

12:47.000 --> 12:48.290
Hey, Mama.

12:48.290 --> 12:51.290
There's something
I'd like to say.

12:51.290 --> 12:53.670
Look, I'm --
I'm not here to judge you.

12:53.670 --> 12:55.620
I'm...

12:55.620 --> 12:57.580
I'm here to forgive you
for, you know...

12:59.420 --> 13:01.960
...your affair.

13:01.960 --> 13:04.080
Forgive me?

13:04.080 --> 13:06.460
I don't need you
to forgive me.

13:06.460 --> 13:09.170
Andre, men look at me.

13:09.170 --> 13:10.460
They desire me.

13:10.460 --> 13:12.830
Their eyes roam my body
and --

13:12.830 --> 13:13.920
Okay, Mama,
I don't -- I don't --

13:13.920 --> 13:15.210
I don't need
to hear any more.

13:15.210 --> 13:17.000
Yeah, well, good,
'cause I was 'bout to get dirty.

13:17.000 --> 13:18.670
[ Sighs ]

13:18.670 --> 13:21.170
Look, whatever happened
back in the day

13:21.170 --> 13:22.790
is none of my business.

13:22.790 --> 13:26.170
And I'm sorry that
I blew up at you like that.

13:26.170 --> 13:27.290
I guess
I was just shocked

13:27.290 --> 13:29.880
because I always think of you
as perfect.

13:29.880 --> 13:33.330
Baby, ain't nothing perfect
'cept Jesus.

13:33.330 --> 13:35.080
And Luther Vandross'
first album.

13:35.080 --> 13:36.290
Mm.
 [ Chuckles ]

13:36.290 --> 13:38.830
But I like
that you saw me that way.

13:40.790 --> 13:43.750
You know, Mama,
maybe this'll be better for us.

13:43.750 --> 13:46.960
You know, me seeing you
as a real person.

13:46.960 --> 13:49.830
Yeah, but I don't want you
thinking I had loose morals.

13:49.830 --> 13:53.250
I really did love
your science teacher.

13:53.250 --> 13:55.960
Gym teacher, Mama.

13:55.960 --> 13:58.420
Oh, yeah -- gym teacher.
Yeah.

13:58.420 --> 14:00.380
Definitely, there was
only one teacher.

14:00.380 --> 14:01.420
Ooh.

14:01.420 --> 14:02.920
You won that science fair
on your own.

14:02.920 --> 14:04.420
Yes, you did.

14:04.420 --> 14:07.250
Ruby: Oh, who's the winner?
Yes!

14:07.250 --> 14:08.920
Say cheese!

14:08.920 --> 14:10.500
Yes!

14:10.500 --> 14:11.790
Mmm!

14:11.790 --> 14:13.040
Mmm!

14:13.040 --> 14:14.380
[ Voice breaking ]
Damn it, Mama,

14:14.380 --> 14:16.710
did I earn
  any of my grades?

14:16.710 --> 14:17.580
Hm?

14:17.580 --> 14:20.580
♪♪

14:20.580 --> 14:23.250
Let's make sure
I don't see your face again.

14:23.250 --> 14:25.580
You won't.
And I am so sorry.

14:25.580 --> 14:27.580
And thank you so much
for bringing her home safely.

14:27.580 --> 14:29.290
I really appreciate it.
Thank you.

14:29.290 --> 14:30.460
Thank you.

14:32.290 --> 14:34.210
Zoey,
what were you thinking?

14:34.210 --> 14:36.170
You're lucky
they didn't put you in jail!

14:36.170 --> 14:39.080
You could've blown everything --
been expelled from school,

14:39.080 --> 14:41.290
put your whole college
acceptance in jeopardy.

14:41.290 --> 14:42.620
But I didn't do anything.

14:42.620 --> 14:45.790
Zoey, they do not
bring kids home in police cars

14:45.790 --> 14:47.290
who didn't do anything!

14:47.290 --> 14:49.330
You're on your way to college,
young lady!
 Yeah.

14:49.330 --> 14:51.750
No, you need to make
better choices!

14:51.750 --> 14:54.000
I'm so mad at you! I can't even
look at you right now!

14:54.000 --> 14:55.960
Go to your room!
Go!

14:55.960 --> 14:57.750
Where are you going?!
 To my room!

14:57.750 --> 14:59.330
Right, yes!
You go to your room!

14:59.330 --> 15:00.750
And where's your brother?

15:00.750 --> 15:01.830
Ma'am?
 Yes? [ Gasps ]

15:01.830 --> 15:03.330
Is this your son?

15:03.330 --> 15:05.330
Yes, it's --
this is my son.

15:05.330 --> 15:06.290
He just turned himself in
to me.

15:06.290 --> 15:07.330
Oh, my God.

15:07.330 --> 15:09.330
Apparently,
he accidentally got high,

15:09.330 --> 15:11.170
and he liked it.

15:11.170 --> 15:13.500
I did.

15:13.500 --> 15:15.000
[ Voice breaking ]
I'm a user.
 Oh, God.

15:15.000 --> 15:16.960
Thank you, thank you so much,
gentlemen, again.

15:16.960 --> 15:18.830
Thank you again.

15:18.830 --> 15:21.080
Wha-- Where -- Where are
your shoes, sweetheart?

15:21.080 --> 15:22.750
[ Crying ] Mommy!

15:22.750 --> 15:23.710
Sweetheart, what?

15:25.830 --> 15:27.500
I should've
taken you dancing.

15:27.500 --> 15:29.170
♪♪

15:29.170 --> 15:31.880
[ Both laughing ]
 [ TV plays indistinctly ]

15:31.880 --> 15:33.120
Hey. What are
you guys watching?

15:33.120 --> 15:34.540
Nothing.
 [ TV shuts off ]

15:34.540 --> 15:36.580
Come on. You don't have to be
like that, all right?

15:36.580 --> 15:38.540
I'm with you guys.

15:38.540 --> 15:41.290
I know Mom's not a saint.

15:41.290 --> 15:42.960
I told you telling him
was a big mistake.

15:42.960 --> 15:44.290
Listen,
I regretted it instantly.

15:44.290 --> 15:46.040
I thought he was strong enough
to handle it.

15:46.040 --> 15:47.040
Men are weak.

15:47.040 --> 15:48.960
Look, Pops.

15:48.960 --> 15:51.120
Man, I blamed you
for everything

15:51.120 --> 15:52.670
that went down growing up.

15:52.670 --> 15:54.380
Why didn't you ever
tell me the truth?

15:54.380 --> 15:55.500
Because you were always
such a mama's boy, Dre.

15:55.500 --> 15:56.920
[ Sighs ]

15:56.920 --> 15:59.170
Look, you needed your mama
to be a saint,

15:59.170 --> 16:01.330
and it takes
a special kind of monster

16:01.330 --> 16:03.500
to ruin a mama
for a mama's boy.

16:03.500 --> 16:05.830
Pops, can you stop
calling me a mama's boy?

16:05.830 --> 16:06.960
Come on, Dre.

16:06.960 --> 16:08.040
All he's trying to say

16:08.040 --> 16:09.460
is that he wasn't
gonna vilify Mom,

16:09.460 --> 16:10.750
because you're --
 You're a mama's boy.

16:10.750 --> 16:12.580
Hey!
 Yeah.

16:12.580 --> 16:15.330
You should've at least
told me about Mama.

16:15.330 --> 16:19.040
No. It was right
that I took the hit on that.

16:19.040 --> 16:21.250
It's part of being
a good father.

16:21.250 --> 16:22.790
He looked out for us,
Dre.

16:22.790 --> 16:24.210
He only let it slip
about Mom

16:24.210 --> 16:26.040
when we went scotch tasting
last year.

16:26.040 --> 16:27.750
Scotch tasting?

16:27.750 --> 16:28.790
I love scotch.

16:28.790 --> 16:30.080
No, you don't.

16:30.080 --> 16:32.420
Yeah, you're more of like a --
a lychee martini guy.

16:32.420 --> 16:33.380
Eh --

16:33.380 --> 16:34.790
A man can't be both?

16:34.790 --> 16:37.040
No.

16:37.040 --> 16:38.750
Look at your brother.

16:38.750 --> 16:40.210
Look at that!

16:40.210 --> 16:42.580
You were so busy partying
and getting arrested

16:42.580 --> 16:46.000
that your brother
 ate 13 marijuana chips!

16:46.000 --> 16:47.750
19.
 Oh, my God.

16:47.750 --> 16:50.000
Zoey, you were supposed to be
watching him!

16:50.000 --> 16:51.710
No, I wasn't.

16:51.710 --> 16:54.380
You made me take him --
and probably to spy on me.

16:54.380 --> 16:56.290
No! No!

16:56.290 --> 16:57.670
M--

16:57.670 --> 16:58.960
Maybe.

16:58.960 --> 17:01.540
Yes, I did.
Okay?

17:01.540 --> 17:05.040
But obviously, you were the one
that needed watching.

17:05.040 --> 17:06.920
No, she didn't!
 Huh?

17:06.920 --> 17:09.170
Zoey's the only reason
I didn't die.

17:09.170 --> 17:11.920
She calmed me down,
got me water,

17:11.920 --> 17:14.540
and protected me
while I made myself vulnerable

17:14.540 --> 17:16.619
to blackmail
and impeachment.

17:16.619 --> 17:18.170
She did?
 Yeah.

17:18.170 --> 17:19.579
She wasn't even drinking.

17:19.579 --> 17:20.829
And only got caught

17:20.829 --> 17:23.290
because she stayed
to help me find my shoes.

17:23.290 --> 17:25.250
[ Gasps deeply ]
 What?

17:25.250 --> 17:26.880
I forgot
my party cloak!

17:26.880 --> 17:28.170
[ Gasps ]

17:28.170 --> 17:29.710
Why do I always
have to showboat?

17:29.710 --> 17:31.380
Oh, boy.

17:31.380 --> 17:34.000
Mom, I don't know why
you're on me all of a sudden,

17:34.000 --> 17:36.250
but I haven't done anything
that bad.

17:36.250 --> 17:39.170
Why would you assume
I'm so terrible?

17:39.170 --> 17:41.120
Sweetie, I know
you're not terrible.

17:41.120 --> 17:42.290
But you're leaving soon.

17:42.290 --> 17:44.880
Mm-hmm.
 And I'm scared.

17:44.880 --> 17:47.250
I am scared
about what might happen

17:47.250 --> 17:49.330
if I'm not with you
every day.

17:49.330 --> 17:52.880
I still see you
as a little girl, even though...

17:52.880 --> 17:54.920
I know you haven't been that
for years.

17:54.920 --> 17:56.710
You've changed,
but it's just hard

17:56.710 --> 17:59.710
for me to see you
as something different.

17:59.710 --> 18:02.540
My God, sweetheart,
you are 17 years old,

18:02.540 --> 18:05.790
which makes me,
like, so ancient.

18:05.790 --> 18:09.380
It's so hard to think of me
that way because I'm --

18:09.380 --> 18:12.330
I'm so young
and -- and hip.

18:12.330 --> 18:14.790
Yeah. Hip people
always say they're hip.

18:14.790 --> 18:15.830
That's what I thought.
 Yeah.

18:15.830 --> 18:17.290
♪♪

18:17.290 --> 18:19.460
I can't believe the police
brought my kids home.

18:19.460 --> 18:21.420
Dre, I told you
the kids are fine.

18:21.420 --> 18:22.880
I don't care
about them kids.

18:22.880 --> 18:24.710
What?
 It's the neighbors.

18:24.710 --> 18:27.000
That Nextdoor app
is buzzing with racism.

18:27.000 --> 18:28.330
Yeah, well,
you know what?

18:28.330 --> 18:32.580
I just feel bad, because Zoey is
a really good kid,

18:32.580 --> 18:34.540
and I was trying to
convince myself that she wasn't.

18:34.540 --> 18:38.080
I mean, it didn't help that
the police brought her home,

18:38.080 --> 18:41.750
but I don't know why
I assume the worst about her.

18:41.750 --> 18:43.290
You label people, Bow.

18:43.290 --> 18:44.880
When you get an idea
about a person,

18:44.880 --> 18:46.460
it's hard for you
to see the reality,

18:46.460 --> 18:49.500
and you end up missing
the obvious clues.
 Uh-huh.

18:49.500 --> 18:52.330
Like perfect strangers
at Thanksgiving

18:52.330 --> 18:56.710
or getting an "A" in gym
for running a 30-minute mile.

18:56.710 --> 18:58.170
Okay, I don't know what
you're talking about anymore.

18:58.170 --> 18:59.500
Not my mom.

18:59.500 --> 19:02.000
She's the exact same woman
I always thought she was.

19:02.000 --> 19:03.750
All right,
men don't look at her.

19:03.750 --> 19:04.790
She has no needs.

19:04.790 --> 19:05.670
She's a saint.

19:05.670 --> 19:06.670
Good night, Bow.

19:06.670 --> 19:08.620
Good night, sweetheart.

19:08.620 --> 19:10.080
[ Muffled crying ]

19:12.460 --> 19:13.830
Are you crying?

19:13.830 --> 19:14.830
Yes.

19:14.830 --> 19:15.830
No.

19:15.830 --> 19:17.380
[ Crying continues ]

19:19.080 --> 19:20.670
Oh, my God.

19:20.670 --> 19:22.750
[ Crying continues ]

19:26.830 --> 19:28.330
♪ Tell me when to go ♪

19:28.330 --> 19:30.830
Pops! Rhonda!
 [ Doorbell rings ]

19:30.830 --> 19:32.750
We talked about this!
Open up!

19:32.750 --> 19:34.330
Can I help you, boss?

19:34.330 --> 19:36.120
What are you doing here?
 [ Music stops ]

19:36.120 --> 19:37.380
Nothing.

19:37.380 --> 19:39.080
You two are
supposed to be in bed.

19:39.080 --> 19:40.210
Get out of here!

19:40.210 --> 19:42.290
Oh. Suddenly,
someone notices us.

19:42.290 --> 19:43.210
Yeah, okay.

19:43.210 --> 19:44.620
Pops is gonna give you
a whuppin'

19:44.620 --> 19:46.040
for being in his house.

19:47.420 --> 19:48.540
♪ Tell me when to go ♪

19:48.540 --> 19:50.170
♪ Tell me when to go ♪

19:50.170 --> 19:52.040
Pops!

19:52.040 --> 19:53.750
Rhonda, you in there?

19:53.750 --> 19:55.080
Rhonda: No!
